replies.body: Hi Alex. Have you seen [this discussion](http://www.grasshopper3d.com/group/ladybug/forum/topics/ladybug-installation-problems)? Can you run GHPython on your machine with no issue?

No. I tried many times. Once I ran the GhPython.gha, the entire GH and Rhino will be halted and down. Then I will find the GhPython.gha in the trash box. I am sure the problem comes from GhPython.gha but don't know how to rectify it.
It can have different reasons. The most common one is that GHPython is blocked. Also make sure you're using 64bit version of Rhino and Rhino and Grasshopper are updated.

I am using 64 bit version.



Should I reinstall grasshopper? But how can I uninstall it?

Hi Alex,

For uninstall the grasshopper ,

You can find grasshopper plugin in this path and if it's needed delete grasshopper folder.

C:\Program Files\Common Files\McNeel\Rhinoceros\5.0\Plug-ins.

Then, Install latest version of the grasshopper again.

Regards,



-Omid
